content.raw:
It's faster to pre-allocate large vectors outside the loop:
~~
N = 2000;
% Initialize the command scalar structure.
cmd.ref_pos = zeros(N, 1);
cmd.ref_vel = zeros(N, 1);
cmd.gain_pos = zeros(N, 1);
cmd.gain_vel = zeros(N, 1);
for counter = 0:N-1
  % Create a new command based on a sinusoidal wave.
  …
  pause(0.001);
end
~~
Update: I misread the code, the counter loop is fine, but we can still pre-allocate the vectors.
~~~
while counter < 2000
  % Initialize the command scalar structure.
  cmd = struct();
  cmd.ref_pos = zeros(deviceInfo.nmotor, 1);
  cmd.ref_vel = cmd.ref_pos;
  cmd.gain_pos = cmd.ref_pos;
  cmd.gain_vel = cmd.ref_pos;
...
~~~
